metadata.name: On Time #188
metadata.description:
[ CLICK TO START THE SOUND ]

Often, I find myself feeling like I'm running behind, or that time is slipping away too quickly. I struggle to be present in the moment because of anxieties related to the past or the future.

"On Time" explores the elusive nature of time and my relationship with it. Through this project, I aimed to create an experience that captures the way that we each experience time in our own way. Seeing that time is not linear but instead, it ebbs and flows in different ways.

At the heart of the experience is a visual reminder to stay in the moment and embrace it. The project consists of 256 unique visuals, each one representing a fleeting moment that has been captured in digital form. These moments are presented in a way that allows you to observe them, appreciate them, and stay present in them. "On Time" is an invitation to pause, take a deep breath, and remind ourselves that we are always where we need to be.

Controls
[ f ] - fullscreen
[ s ] - save the current frame as an image

Created with Three.js

metadata.name: Anachronous #173
metadata.description:
This project is about the exploration of chaotic structures created with lines and blurry silhouettes. They work together to make the shapes emerge without revealing them completely and create dark and light areas that compose a feeling of depth and weight to the scene.

Some pieces are chaotic, some more ordered. Some have strong compositions, some don't. By zooming in on the details we can let our mind wander and start seeing shapes.

Best experienced in full-screen.

Press S to take a screenshot
Press M to take a high resolution screenshot
Press H to take a higher resolution screenshot (may not work for some devices)

WARNING: Project is using webgl, it may not work on some older devices.

Original artwork by William Watkins · Lyon, 2022

metadata.name: Bunny on Shrooms #36
metadata.description:
Bunny on Shrooms is a generative shader experiment: what happens when the Stanford bunny munches on the psychedelic fungus?  Each time she eats mushrooms, her buzz is slightly different.  She always gets all wiggly and wavy… but her color story and the rhythms of her psychedelic experience are different on every trip.  

Created by @capnganj - one love <3

metadata.name: QUE DU BRUIT, VARIATION NOIRE #10
metadata.description:
Pour créer cette proposition, j'ai utilisé du bruit VHS, en jouant avec la saturation et en supprimant certaines données pour créer des zones de transparence.

Le bruit réfère à une poétique politique. Le vacarme est permanent. L'ordre et le silence, improbable.

J'ai retravaillé les couches pour créer cette suite de variations noires.

*

J'utilise le code de PureSpider pour travailler les couches d'images.

metadata.name: Acid Drops #20
metadata.description:
Acid Drops is an algorithm that generates drops of LSD.  Each drop contains a colorful, silly, sometimes-scary little psychedelic world that is waiting to unfurl.  The drops are all spheres of exactly the same size, but each one dances around differently and refracts glimpses of a future psychedelic colorscape.

Created by @capnganj - one love <3

metadata.name: Amalgam #19
metadata.description:
What happens when a flow field moves through some polygons scattered on the canvas?
Three variables, noise scale, step size and the alpha value of the particles moving through the flow field determine the kind of output you see.
In some cases, polygons stand their ground and are clearly visible but in some cases the field moves so fast that you can't even make the outline of the shapes.

Controls:
s save at any moment
p pause rendering
r restart rendering
1 render in 1024 x 1024 (default)
2 render in 2048 x 2048
3 render in 4096 x 4096

metadata.name: Reblend #43
metadata.description:
There are two creative features to this project.
The first feature is related to the production of colors at random points, so that geometric shapes are placed in proper harmony with each other and then allowed to process and produce colors at the intersection.
The second feature is the subtraction of a part of the shapes that are located in the center, and in the place of subtraction, geometric shapes are replaced, which will produce a new content of regular geometric shapes.
This innovative art not only challenges the traditional concepts of beauty but also encourages the thinking of viewers to combine colors and geometric shapes.

S = Save
Made by p5.js

metadata.name: Garden, Monoliths #25
metadata.description:
"Garden, Monoliths" is the result of an algorithm that started in April 2021. It was called "Grass.js".
Spring was blooming all around the house, taking over the stones and remnants of ancient battles that stood here. Inspiration was everywhere.
The initial goal was to use mathematical formulas for creating patterns inspired by the density of nature, that could be used by a pen plotter, so it kept focusing on outputting vector lines. This history and practice produced a graphical style based on line strokes, plus occasionally some transparent, filled shapes.
Each artwork will be either "Garden" or "Monolith", for they are variations of two existing designs from the workshop.
